2756 /// This provides a uniform API for creating instructions and inserting
2757 /// them into a basic block: either at the end of a BasicBlock, or at a specific
2758 /// iterator location in a block.
2759 ///
2760 /// Note that the builder does not expose the full generality of LLVM
2761 /// instructions.  For access to extra instruction properties, use the mutators
2762 /// (e.g. setVolatile) on the instructions after they have been
2763 /// created. Convenience state exists to specify fast-math flags and fp-math
2764 /// tags.
2765 ///
2766 /// The first template argument specifies a class to use for creating constants.
2767 /// This defaults to creating minimally folded constants.  The second template
2768 /// argument allows clients to specify custom insertion hooks that are called on
2769 /// every newly created insertion.
